What you need to know:

Farmers have started harvesting the main season crop in most parts of the North Rift with the exercise expected to peak next month.President Uhuru Kenyatta last month directed the Ministry of Agriculture to ensure that farmers are paid a minimum of Sh2,500 per bag for their maize.Mr Kenyatta also issued several other directives aimed at safeguarding farmers and enhancing their income, which included lowering of the drying and storage charges at the National Cereals and Produce Board.